<h1>Little Bookniks</h1>
<h3 class="subheading">Festival Curation and Outreach</h3>


<h2>The Brief:</h2>

<p>Little Bookniks was a successful literature festival for families with a focus on Jewish story-telling. The festival was delivered  by three main partners (JCC, Jewish Book Week and the Jewish Museum). The brief was to widen and diversity partipation in the festival.</p>


<h2>Putting it into action:</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Programming Little Booknik's participative strand, which included 'hands on' workshops in claymation, puppetry and audio-art.</li>

    <li>Highlighted no-cost 'entry points' to the festival, including free workshop activities and exhibitions.</li>

    <li>Identified key project funders and stakeholders who would support subsiding ticket costs.</li>

    <li>Pioneered the Festival's first schools outreach programme which involved partnership with 3 local Camden based primary schools and the curation of the children's work at the Jewish museum.</li>

    <li>Developed marketing, documentation and project evaluation.</li>

    <li>Budgetary management.</li>
</ul>

